<h2>Delivery Roadmap</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Phase</th><th>Weeks</th><th>Focus</th><th>Deliverables</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>1 — Foundation</b></td><td>1–2</td><td>Repo, conventions, template, install scripts, security guardrails</td><td>Working repo skeleton anyone can install from</td></tr>
<tr class="alt"><td><b>2 — Data Platform pilots</b></td><td>2–4</td><td><code>airflow-dag-health</code>, <code>snowflake-cost-audit</code>, <code>databricks-job-triage</code></td><td>3 skills in daily use by pilot group</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>3 — Rollout + DevOps/DE tracks</b></td><td>4–8</td><td>Team onboarding; first DevOps skills (<code>ci-failure-triage</code>, <code>terraform-plan-review</code>) and DE skills (<code>sql-review</code>, <code>spark-job-tuner</code>); expand Track 1 by team vote</td><td>10–15 skills live; contribution workflow running</td></tr>
<tr class="alt"><td><b>4 — Cross-cutting + Delivery track</b></td><td>8+</td><td><code>pipeline-incident-triage</code>, <code>daily-data-ops-report</code>, Jira integration, client-delivery skills</td><td>Flagship cross-tool automations; org-wide adoption</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>5 — Native ecosystem pilot</b></td><td>Parallel to Phase 3+</td><td>Audit coco-skills/Databricks skills for reuse; dual-publish one pilot skill (e.g. <code>snowflake-cost-audit</code>) to Cortex Agents</td><td>One skill running in both Claude Code and a native platform agent</td></tr>
</table>
<p><b>Prioritization principle within every track:</b> triage &amp; reporting skills first (daily pain, read-only, safe), generators second, write-capable skills last and always confirmation-gated.</p>

<h2>Skill Count Summary</h2>
